Patch Set 2:

Logic looks good.

Any reason not to put the check in 'def update' in glance/api/v1/images.py? (We seem to do some other roughly similar enforcement there.)

Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

If I may ask, since V1 is not under active development any more, is there a really strong reason why we want this in v1? 

As I see this, it is just fixing the return codes, though meaningful I'm not convinced if this MUST get into v1. Help me understand if I'm missing anything here.

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

@Hemanth

This may be a good topic for the weekly meeting ("what changes are we currently accepting for v1"?).

I'm not sure why we wouldn't continue to accept bug fixes (particularly if they're small/well scoped) while we're still releasing with v1.

Patch Set 3:

My personal take here is to fix the 500 condition. The side effect of changing that 200 to 403 might be stretching it to the point we cannot accept. 

V1 api is still supported so the actual failures we must be willing to fix.
